    <briefdescription>
<para>Get a common integer for an operation between type A and B. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This template provides a convenient way to find a safe common integer type for an integer operation. Compared with <computeroutput>std::common_type</computeroutput> it does not allow mixing of signed and unsigned integers. Compared with <computeroutput>std::common_type</computeroutput> it handles <computeroutput>uint16_t</computeroutput> as 16bit values if the implementation allows it. The result is <computeroutput>type</computeroutput>, which is only a valid integer if both type A and B are integer and are compatible for a safe operation. See <computeroutput>IntegerMath.hpp</computeroutput> for mixed operations and comparisons. <parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>A</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The first integer type. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>B</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The second integer type. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
